Description of the new species.
Animals (measurements and statistics in 
Table 3
). Body white in living specimens and transparent after fixation (
Figs 1–3
). Eyes absent after fixation in all studied specimens. Cuticle smooth, i.e. without gibbosities, papillae, spines, sculpturing or pores. Granulation present on external cuticle of all legs (
Figs 4–9
). Under SEM granulation visible as aggregates consisted of two to a dozen or so microgranules (
Figs 6, 9
).

